<subSubSection id="C31F65574D73FFFA43B4CA983FD0F8D7" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BBA36DC4D73FFFA43B4CA983D6BFA07" blockId="54.[151,1436,1446,1903]" box="[151,260,1446,1471]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<heading id="D0F281B04D73FFFA43B4CA983D6BFA07" bold="true" box="[151,260,1446,1471]" fontSize="10" level="2" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" reason="2">
<emphasis id="B971EACE4D73FFFA43B4CA983D6BFA07" bold="true" box="[151,260,1446,1471]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBA36DC4D73FFFA43B4CAF43EEAF9CB" blockId="54.[151,1436,1446,1903]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
When 
<bibRefCitation id="EF944B2D4D73FFFA43C5CAF43DB4FA5B" author="Cockerell, T. D. A." box="[230,475,1482,1507]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" pagination="1 - 15" refId="ref45747" refString="Cockerell, T. D. A. (1942) Bees of the family Hylaeidae from the Ethiopian Region. Smithsonian Miscellaneous Collections, 101, 1 - 15." type="journal article" year="1942">Cockerell (1942: 14)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="4C054D5F4D73FFFA417DCAF43F44FA5B" authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1942" box="[606,811,1482,1507]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simulans">
<emphasis id="B971EACE4D73FFFA417DCAF43F44FA5B" box="[606,811,1482,1507]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Hylaeus simulans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a new species from R.E. Turner’s &quot;Series 7&quot;, he designated Mossel Bay (
<collectingRegion id="49C1F83E4D73FFFA429BCAD03E0AF9BF" box="[440,613,1518,1543]" country="South Africa" name="Western Cape" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Cape Province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F312764C4D73FFFA4156CAD03F63F9BF" box="[629,780,1518,1543]" name="South Africa" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">South Africa</collectingCountry>
) as the type locality, but mentioning also an additional location, Katberg (
<collectingRegion id="49C1F83E4D73FFFA424AC92C3E7AF993" box="[361,533,1554,1579]" country="South Africa" name="Western Cape" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Cape Province</collectingRegion>
). The type series of 
<taxonomicName id="4C054D5F4D73FFFA41D9C92D3FAFF993" authority="Ckll." authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1942" box="[762,960,1554,1579]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simulans">
<emphasis id="B971EACE4D73FFFA41D9C92D3FEEF993" box="[762,897,1554,1579]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">H. simulans</emphasis>
Ckll.
</taxonomicName>
is preserved in the London collection and consists of the 
<typeStatus id="54BE887E4D73FFFA421FC9083DCEF9F7" box="[316,417,1590,1615]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">holotype</typeStatus>
, type specimen no. 17.a.1404, and 
<specimenCount id="9D03FD554D73FFFA400BC9083FA7F9F7" box="[808,968,1590,1615]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" type="generic" typeStatus="paratypes">four paratypes</specimenCount>
which all originate from Mossel Bay, and there is 
<specimenCount id="9D03FD554D73FFFA43CCC9653D04F9CB" box="[239,363,1626,1651]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
<typeStatus id="54BE887E4D73FFFA4251C9653DB1F9CB" box="[370,478,1627,1651]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">paratypus</typeStatus>
from Katberg.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBA36DC4D73FFFA43E4C9403FD0F8D7" blockId="54.[151,1436,1446,1903]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
Recently D. Notton located in the NHML collection another female from Katberg, collected by R.E. Turner and obviously belonging to that Series 7, but without a name label. The two available females from Katberg, one of them a 
<typeStatus id="54BE887E4D73FFFA43D2C9F93D31F967" box="[241,350,1735,1759]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">paratypus</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C054D5F4D73FFFA42A9C9F93E7BF967" authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1942" box="[394,532,1734,1759]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simulans">
<emphasis id="B971EACE4D73FFFA42A9C9F93E7BF967" box="[394,532,1734,1759]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">H. simulans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, are obviously specimens of an undescribed species. They differ from the 
<taxonomicName id="4C054D5F4D73FFFA46A2C9F93C94F8BB" authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1942" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simulans">
<emphasis id="B971EACE4D73FFFA46A2C9F93C94F8BB" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">H. simulans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
type series primarily by their round face and the fine punctation of T2. Although the tergite punctation varies among specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C054D5F4D73FFFA42C0C8313E01F89F" authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1942" box="[483,622,1806,1831]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simulans">
<emphasis id="B971EACE4D73FFFA42C0C8313E01F89F" box="[483,622,1806,1831]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">H. simulans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[now 
<taxonomicName id="4C054D5F4D73FFFA419CC8313FB1F89F" authority="(Alfken)" baseAuthorityName="Alfken" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[703,990,1806,1831]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugipunctus">
<emphasis id="B971EACE4D73FFFA419CC8313F02F89E" box="[703,877,1807,1830]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">H. rugipunctus</emphasis>
(Alfken)
</taxonomicName>
], the difference to the new species is substantial. Moreover it is striking that 
<taxonomicName id="4C054D5F4D73FFFA4179C80D3E8EF8F3" authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1942" box="[602,737,1842,1867]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simulans">
<emphasis id="B971EACE4D73FFFA4179C80D3E8EF8F3" box="[602,737,1842,1867]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">H. simulans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was captured in March and April at sea level, while the new species was found in November at an altitude of 
<quantity id="4CFD9B394D73FFFA419AC8683F4DF8D7" box="[697,802,1878,1903]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2192" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" unit="ft" value="4000.0">4000 feet</quantity>
(ca. 
<quantity id="4CFD9B394D73FFFA4079C8683FDCF8D7" box="[858,947,1878,1903]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" unit="m" value="1200.0">1200 m</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
